<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1622" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1622">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/133.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 204.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my despatch No. 194 of the
                            24th ultimo as to negotiations proceeding between Señor Carlos
                            Constantino Arosemena, Minister of Public Works, and Messrs. J. M. Hyatt
                            and Robert Wilcox, relative to the signature of the contract between the
                            Panaman Government and these gentlemen for the construction of a railway
                            from Antón to Santiago, etc., I have the honor to inform you <pb facs="1322" n="1206" xml:id="pg_1206"/> that Señor Chiarí, Minister
                            of Foreign Affairs, has now advised mo that the contract will not be
                            signed by this administration, which, owing to the fact that it is so
                            near its expiration, will not sign any more contracts, believing this to
                            be improper.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">F. Percival Dodge.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>